Staff Reporter
One of Zimbabwe’s leading economist and commentator, John Robertson has died. Robinson died this morning at his home in Harare after suffering a stroke several weeks ago. Born 1937 in Bulawayo, Robertson trained at the Technical College and later became a technician with the Air Force, specialising in radio communications.  As a mature student, he enrolled  at the University of Rhodesia and obtained an honours degree in economics from London University. John will be remembered as a fine economist who always supported his opinions and views with substantial research and statistics. He is survived by two sons.